<headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 31 at 3:30PM CDT  by NWS Brownsville</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Hidalgo
County through 400 PM CDT...
At 330 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Maria Alicia P Munoz Elementary School, or near Donna, moving north
at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Edinburg, Pharr, Weslaco, San Juan, Alamo, Donna, Mercedes, Elsa,
Progreso and Edcouch.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
